                'rss_feed_enabled'                  => true,
                'website_content'                   => '<div>I have a rather unique viewpoint of serverless in general, and of PHP serverless in particular.&nbsp;<br><br>A viewpoint that I express in my podcasts, and in my PHP Serverless Project.&nbsp;<br><br>I have not yet explicitly expressed this viewpoint in one concise podcast, so I wanted to do so now. In this episode, I enumerate the seven things about serverless that I think.</div><div><br><br>1) One, "serverless" is a bullshit marketing term, denoting, neither an actual technology nor actual technological processes.<br><br></div><div>2) "Serverless" is at best a placeholder term for features.</div><div><br>3) The two dominant features are server abstraction and scale.</div><div><br>4) Since serverless denotes features, any technology or platform that delivers server abstraction and or scale are relevant to serverless.</div><div><br>5) Serverless platforms and technologies are not fungible.</div><div><br>6) Since serverless platforms and technologies are not fungible, it is important to understand what use cases any given platform or technology satisfies.</div><div><br>7) Two common characteristics of serverless platforms are. Variably priced, and unable to SSH.<br><br></div>',
